
** Abbreviatons

  - RS  (Row Source)
  - SMJ (Sort Merge Join)

** Operations

  - FTS (Full Table Scan)

  - Index Unique Scan    - looking up single value
  - Index Range Scan     - looking up a range
  - Index Full Scan      - looking up the complete index
  - Index Fast Full Scan - looking up a second column of a composite 
                           index
  - Rowid

  - Sort Merge Join (SMJ)- Sort RS1, SORT RS2, Merge
  - Nested Loops         - LOOP RS1, LOOP RS2
  - Hash Join            - Smaller RS Hash Table, Bigger RS lookup
  - Cartesian Product

  - Sorts (order by, group by, SMJ)

** Other Terms

  - Antijoin - not in
  - Semijoin - exists

** Index Range Scan

  - clustering factor

** Clustering Factor of an Index

  - A lower clustering factor indicates that the rows are in fewer
    blocks (costs less)

